Thai Economy to Grow 3%-5% This Year, Prasarn Says

-- B y   S u t t i n e e   Y u v e j w a t t a n a
-- 
2011-03-28T08:38:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/thai-economy-to-grow-3-5-this-year-prasarn-says-correct-.html
(Corrects growth estimate in headline, first paragraph.)  Rising oil and commodity prices
won’t stop  Thailand ’s economy from growing between 3 percent and
5 percent this year, because the expansion is broad-based,
central bank Governor Prasarn Trairatvorakul said in a speech to
investors today in Bangkok.  To contact the reporter on this story:
